rdf:Description.lla:note: Under 'Date' and 'Port of leaving' 1907-03-05 and Falmouth have been crossed out

Report of accident off Mounts Bay, nr. Newlyn, when E.L. was thrown into the water by the main sheet and was drowned. Some dispute about his surname, but Lashmar believed to be correct. Also about his age, 1885 also possible.
New Master Bate states that Stevens left before he joined and so he cannot give particulars.
